########################################################################
#
#   Monit PACKAGES
#
########################################################################

This file lists known monit packages, their packagers and where to find
them. Some can be found mirrored to fsf.org.

Many packages listed here are individual contributions. 
Please, don't expect those to stem from quality build control systems 
as can be expected from your fave distributor. In doubt, please rebuild 
them on your box.

Monit's download area at fsf.org:
http://freesoftware.fsf.org/download/monit/


Packages overview:

 o ALTLinux
 o Debian
 o Gentoo
 o OpenBSD
 o OpenPKG
 o PLD
 o Redhat and Fedora
 o Solaris
 o SuSE
 o Yoper


------------------------------------------------------------------------
ALTLinux (included in current distribution) - i586
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Packager:   Igor Homyakov <homyakov@ramax.spb.ru>

URL:        http://altlinux.com/index.php?module=sisyphus&package=monit

Install:    apt-get install monit


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Debian (included in testing distribution)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Packager:   Fredrik Steen <stone@debian.org>

URL:        http://packages.debian.org/testing/admin/monit

Install:    apt-get -t testing install monit


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gentoo (included in current distribution)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

URL:        http://www.gentoo.org

Install:    emerge app-admin/monit


------------------------------------------------------------------------
OpenBSD (included in current distribution)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

URL:        http://www.openbsd.org


